# Phase closeout playbook mode (requestable)

When the operator is **closing a phase** and preparing a **release**:

1. Open and follow **`.ai/playbooks/phase-closeout-and-release.md`** (playbook id `phase-closeout-and-release`). Prefer attaching that file (`@`) so steps stay in context.
2. Use **`.ai/agent-source-of-truth-order.md`** for agent precedence and **`.ai/AGENT-CLI-MAP.md`** for every **`workspace-kit run`** line that mutates kit-owned state.
3. **Policy:** sensitive `workspace-kit run` commands require JSON **`policyApproval`** in the third CLI argument; `config` / `init` / `upgrade` use env approval per **`.ai/POLICY-APPROVAL.md`**. Chat-only approval does not satisfy policy.
4. **Human gate:** do not publish or run release automation until explicit human approval — see **`.ai/RELEASING.md`**.
5. After publish, end with the playbook’s **§7 Phase delivery summary** copy-paste template **verbatim shape**: short lines and **`{placeholders}`** only — no long parentheticals in the template body. Counts come from **`list-tasks`** / task store + phase metadata (**`get-next-actions`**, status YAML, or maintainer-agreed phase fields), not memory. This is **not** JSON **`responseTemplateId`** on **`wk run`**.

Invocation options and limits of auto-loading: **`.ai/runbooks/agent-playbooks.md`**.

This rule does **not** override **`maintainer-delivery-loop.mdc`** or **`workspace-kit-cli-execution.mdc`**; it points at the same playbook and policy surfaces.
